A: The problem is that you are calling `it.next()` inside the loop, which means you are only ever getting the first child of the DataSnapshot. You should be getting the value of the current DataSnapshot in the loop, like this:

```java
for(Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ){
    i = i + 1;
    names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
}
```

This will add the value of each child to the names list.

Also, you can simplify your code by using a foreach loop:

```java
int i = 0;
